traceability.evidence:
In src/print-outdated.js at the age-filtering step, the code filters only on the age of info.latest:

  // Filter by age threshold
  const matureRows = rows.filter(([_name, , , , age, depType]) => {
    const minAge = depType === 'prod' ? prodMinAge : devMinAge;
    return typeof age === 'number' && age >= minAge;
  });

This only checks the latest version’s age and does not implement the “smart filtering” requirement to iterate backwards through published versions until finding the first one ≥7 days old. Consequently, if the very latest version is too new but an earlier version is mature, it won’t be selected. No code handles selecting a non-latest mature version.
